[[Category:Peperomia|*]] [[Category:Lists of plant species|Peperomia]]

The '''Marathon Large Igneous Province''' is a [[Paleoproterozoic]] [[large igneous province]] along the southern [[Superior craton]] of [[Ontario]], Canada, located around the northern margin of [[Lake Superior]]. It consists of three [[diabase]] [[dike swarm]]s known as Marathon, Kapuskasing and Fort Frances. The Kapuskasing and Marathon dike swarms range in age from about 2,126&nbsp;to 2,101&nbsp;million years old while the Fort Frances dike swarm is between 2,076&nbsp;and 2,067&nbsp;million years old.<ref name="SI">{{cite journal|last1=Halls|first1=Henry C.|last2=Davis|first2=D.W.|last3=Stott|first3=G.M.|last4=Ernst|first4=R.E.|last5=Hamilton|first5=M.A.|title=The Paleoproterozoic Marathon Large Igneous Province: New evidence for a 2.1Ga long-lived mantle plume event along the southern margin of the North American Superior Province|journal=Precambrian Research|date=May 2008|volume=162|issue=3–4|pages=327–353|doi=10.1016/j.precamres.2007.10.009}}</ref>

A single, periodically active [[mantle plume]] was responsible for the creation of the Marathon Large Igneous Province due to the lack of apparent [[polar wander]] during the formation of the igneous province.<ref name="SI"/> The large magmatic event covers an area of at least {{Convert|400000|km2|mi2|abbr=on}} and the entire large igneous province was constructed in 60&nbsp;million years.<ref name="SI"/>

